<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Manchester United have set their sights on Ajax defender Nicolas Tagliafico as a possible alternative to Alex Telles.</p>

<p>The Red Devils want to add a new left-back and offer competition to Luke Shaw. </p>

<p>Ole Gunnar Solskjaer missed out on Sergio Reguilon after Tottenham agreed to a buy-back clause with Real Madrid.</p>

<p>Manchester United have set their sights on Ajax defender Nicolas Tagliafico (above)</p>

<p>Manchester United switched their attention to Brazilian Telles, 27, who is into the final year of his contract at Porto.</p>

<p>But the Sun claim the club are also considering Argentine full-back Tagliafico, who is available for around £23m.</p>

<p>The 28-year-old was on Leicester’s shortlist as a replacement for Ben Chilwell, but they oped to sign Atalanta’s Timothy Castagne instead.</p>

<p>Negotiations between United and Porto are said to be ongoing over defender Alex Telles</p>
